  "prompt": "Halloween walk in York?",
  "response": "Yes, York offers a number of spooky and engaging Halloween walks! Here are a few popular options and where to find them:\n\n**Official Ghost Walks (These are the most popular and have been running for decades):**\n\n*   **The Original Ghost Walk of York:** Claims to be the very first ghost walk in York. They usually start from outside the York Minster's West Door (the main entrance). Look for the cloaked guide with the lantern.\n*   **The Ghost Walk of York:** This one starts from The King's Arms pub on the River Ouse.\n*   **The York Ghost Bus Tour:** A theatrical experience on a vintage bus.\n\n**Independent Ghost Walks:**\n\n*   **Mad Alice's York Ghost Walk:** Mad Alice was a real person who was burned at the stake in York. This walk starts from the bottom of the Shambles.\n*   **The Deathly Dark Ghost Walk of York:** Starts near the Golden Fleece pub.\n*   **Shadows of York Ghost Walk:** Meet near the statue of Constantine the Great outside York Minster.\n\n**Things to consider when choosing a walk:**\n\n*   **Reputation:** Check online reviews and ratings of different walks to see what others have experienced.\n*   **Guide Style:** Some guides are more theatrical and comedic, while others are more focused on historical accuracy and serious storytelling. Choose one that suits your preference.\n*   **Route:** Some walks cover specific areas of the city or focus on particular types of hauntings.\n*   **Price:** Prices can vary between walks, so compare before booking.\n*   **Booking:** Some walks require pre-booking, especially during peak times like Halloween. Others operate on a \"turn-up-and-pay\" basis. Check the specific walk's website or social media page.\n*   **Family-Friendliness:** Consider the age and sensitivity of children if you're bringing them along. Some walks might be too scary for younger audiences.\n\n**Tips for a great experience:**\n\n*   **Dress warmly:** Evenings in York can be chilly, especially in October.\n*   **Wear comfortable shoes:** You'll be doing a lot of walking.\n*   **Bring a flashlight (torch):** Some areas can be dark.\n*   **Be respectful of residents:** Keep noise levels down, especially in residential areas.\n*   **Book in advance:** Especially around Halloween, popular walks can sell out.\n\nEnjoy your spooky Halloween walk in York!\n",
